# SEO Content Rules

## Always read before writing content
1. `seo-system/GLOBAL_SEO_CONTENT_RULES.md` — SSoT for all SEO content rules
2. `seo-system/briefs/[slug].yaml` — page-specific intent, sections, cannibalization map
3. Current page file + content file

## 3-step workflow (never skip steps)
- **Step 1:** Analyze + Outline only — no writing yet
- **Step 2:** Edit/create content by section
- **Step 3:** QA audit (scores for 6 dimensions) — mandatory

Full workflow: `seo-system/WORKFLOW.md`
Full task template: `seo-system/CURSOR_TASK_TEMPLATE.md`

## Content language
- All page copy (H1/H2/H3, body, CTA, FAQ, meta title/description): **Dutch (NL)**
- All analysis, outlines, QA reports to owner: **Russian (RU)**

## Non-negotiable constraints
- No fabricated claims, prices, guarantees, certifications
- Uncertainty flags: `[CLAIM_NEEDS_CONFIRMATION]`, `[MISSING_BUSINESS_INPUT]`, `[UNCERTAIN_TERM]`
- Energy savings always conditional: "kan leiden tot", never "leidt tot"
- Check sibling pages for cannibalization (listed in brief under `cannibalization.siblingPages`)
- Preserve existing internal links and JSON-LD — only suggest content-level changes
- Do not touch `lib/seo/meta.ts`, `lib/seo/schema.ts`, `app/sitemap.ts` without explicit request

## Content edit rules
- Edit `lib/content/[slug].ts` when content lives there
- Edit inline in `page.tsx` only when content is not in a separate content file
- Edit section by section — show what changes and why
- Preserve existing good content — do not rewrite what works
